    "Table 1 presents a comparative analysis of the GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 models in the task of automated fact-checking using the PolitiFact dataset.",
    "The table categorizes the performance of both models across different veracity labels ranging from \"pants-fire\" to \"true.\"",
    "In the left table, the accuracy of the model is computed by considering only two categories, i.e., grouping \"pants-fire, \" \"false, \" and \"mostly-false\" together to false and \"half-true, \" \"mostly-true, \" and \"true\" to true.",
    "In the right table, the accuracy is computed using all the PolitiFact categories."
